:::summary
King Arthur is the legendary British ruler whose story — with Guinevere, Lancelot, Merlin, and the Knights of the Round Table — is one of the most enduring and beloved in Western literature. Whether a historical figure, a mythologized memory of a post-Roman British leader, or pure legend, Arthur has captivated poets, writers, and readers for over a thousand years. His quest-driven court and the search for the Holy Grail intersect with Christian themes of redemption, sacrifice, and spiritual aspiration.
:::

